In this speech at the University of Hartford in Connecticut, President Joe Biden addresses the issue of gun violence in the United States. He acknowledges the courage of survivors and advocates who have turned their pain into purpose and their anger into commitment. President Biden highlights the importance of taking action to prevent gun violence and emphasizes the need for bipartisan cooperation. He discusses the Bipartisan Safer Communities Act, which he signed into law, and outlines the measures it includes, such as enhanced background checks and funding for mental health services. President Biden calls for a ban on assault weapons and high-capacity magazines, as well as the end of immunity for gun manufacturers. He urges Congress to pass legislation and states to take action, emphasizing the role of grassroots movements and the power of collective action. President Biden concludes by expressing his determination to continue fighting for gun safety measures and urging others to do the same.